	        If
	the underwriters exercise their option to purchase 432,692 additional shares of our common stock in full at the public offering price of $13.00 per share, the net tangible book value
	per share after giving effect to the offering would be $4.03 per share. This represents an immediate increase in as adjusted net tangible book value of $2.86 per share to existing stockholders and an
	immediate dilution in net tangible book value of $8.97 per share to new investors purchasing shares of our common stock in this offering.




